tr: an analysis (often in graphical form) representing the extent to which something exhibits various characteristics
example: a psychological profile of serial killers

tr: a vertical section of the Earth's crust showing the different horizons or layers
an outline of something (especially a human face as seen from one side)
degree of exposure to public notice
example: that candidate does not have sufficient visibility to win an election

tr: represent in profile, by drawing or painting

example: The author of this article profiles a famous painter

value.def: Your profile is the outline of your face as it is seen when someone is looking at you from the side.

example.ex: His handsome profile was turned away from us.
example.tran: 他英俊的侧影从我们眼前转开了。

value.def: If you see someone in profile, you see them from the side.

example.ex: This picture shows the girl in profile.
example.tran: 这张照片照的是女孩的侧面。

value.def: A profile of someone is a short article or programme in which their life and character are described.

example.ex: A newspaper published profiles of the candidates' wives.
example.tran: 一家报纸刊登了几位候选人夫人的简介。

value.def: To profile someone means to give an account of that person's life and character.

example.ex: Tamar Golan, a Paris-based journalist, profiles the rebel leader.
example.tran: 驻巴黎记者塔玛·戈兰对反叛者的首领进行了介绍。

example.ex: ...a former FBI agent who pioneered psychological profiling in the 1970s.
example.tran: 在20世纪70年代开创了心理画像的前联邦调查局探员

example.ex: DNA profiling has aided the struggle against crime.
example.tran: DNA分析对于打击犯罪有所帮助。

value.def: If someone has a high profile, people notice them and what they do. If you keep a low profile, you avoid doing things that will make people notice you.

example.ex: ...a move that would give Egypt a much higher profile in the upcoming peace talks...
example.tran: 能使埃及在未来的和谈中更加引人关注的举动

example.ex: Football is a high profile business...
example.tran: 足球是一个引人注目的产业。

example.ex: The police deliberately kept a low profile in most places.
example.tran: 警方在大多数地方有意保持低调。

value.tran: 高调/低调；高姿态/低姿态
